sec.p:
The relationship of offspring mass and size to adult weight can also be derived theoretically from previous modeling efforts (Hendriks 2007). The starting point in this model is production because coefficients and slopes of allometric regressions for this parameter differ only slightly for various groups of species. The rate constant for population turnover (production kp), measured as the production/biomass ratio (P/B) (kg kg−1 day−1) is related to adult mass (m) as: 1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
