$$ k_{{\text{p}}} = q_{{\text{T}}} \cdot \gamma _{{\text{p}}} \cdot m^{{ - \kappa }} . $$\end{document}

Production kp is allocated to somatic and gonadic growth. We will consider the rate constant for reproduction (reproduction kpr) to be a fraction (prp) of total production kp according to: 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
